<section
  class="grid-show"
  data-grid-enter="ripple-out"
  data-grid-exit="ripple-out"
  data-stagger-interval="50"
>
  <h2>Grid Background</h2>
  <p>
    A subtle and modern background effect. Just add
    <code>&lt;canvas id="grid-bg"&gt;&lt;/canvas&gt;</code> at the bottom of your app to get
    started.
  </p>
  <p>
    Out of the box this will follow the user's mouse cursor. It will also have an interval that
    shows the grid in an animation of your choice. This is so users without a mouse can still enjoy
    the effect. Current animation options include:
  </p>
  <ul class="classic-list">
    <li><code>stack-top</code></li>
    <li><code>stack-bottom</code></li>
    <li><code>stack-left</code></li>
    <li><code>stack-right</code></li>
    <li><code>ripple-out</code></li>
    <li><code>ripple-in</code></li>
    <li><code>random</code></li>
    <li><code>diag-tl</code></li>
    <li><code>diag-tr</code></li>
    <li><code>diag-br</code></li>
    <li><code>diag-bl</code></li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You can also tack on the util class of <code>grid-show</code> to fade the grid in (as you're
    currently seeing).
  </p>
  <p>Fully configurable with:</p>
  <ul class="classic-list">
    <li><code>data-grid-enter</code> to handle the 'enter' animation.</li>
    <li><code>data-grid-exit</code> to handle the 'exit' animation.</li>
    <li><code>data-stagger-interval</code> a number do alter the animation speed.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

